environmentHooksDescription: Shared Environment hooks allow you to run external automation when an Shared Environment booking becomes active (Shared Environment acquired) or expires (Shared Environment released). You can use them with external systems like Jenkins, GitLab CI, etc.{br}Webhooks send a POST request to the defined URL with the payload containing information about the Shared Environment, the booking, and the user who acquires/releases the Shared Environment.

privacyWarning:
We respect your company’s privacy and believe that cybersecurity is one of the vital things for each company.{br}In regards to that, we request read-only access to your cloud accounts or Kubernetes clusters metrics to be able to read billing data and discover resources.{br}We use billing data to analyze your expenses, show forecasts and identify patterns that can help you optimize your next bills.{br}OptScale discovers resources to identify newly created items, notify you about unused resources or resources with violated TTL.{br}You can learn more about required permissions in our documentation.{br}The only parameter that can be modified in your cloud account and with your permission is a Tags field.{br}{br}The following information is stored internally to deliver the best value of the product:
  • Resource names and billing data
  • Resource tags
  • OptScale configuration, resource pools, and TTL rules
  • List of users in the product

WE DO NOT SHARE YOUR DATA WITH ANY THIRD PARTY OR STORE ANY NETWORK INFORMATION LIKE IP ADDRESSES, SECURITY GROUPS, OR VPC CONFIGURATION.

If you have any questions, please contact us at {email}.
